      "title": "DisCO dancing - Transformative politics of the college",
      "text": "Metaphors of dancing and animated movement run right the way through the design of the college, and through the pattern language of making the living economy which is its core and rationale. Here we outline the most prominent dance metaphors."
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "0cce575d124fae76",
      "text": "Thus:\n- Don’t carve off ‘cultural’ from ‘technical’ or ‘structural’. All are implicated in the dance of knowing and capability, and need to be mobilised in both the design and construction of any given tool and the performing of any capable, literate course of action. For more on this, see [[A hierarchy of infrastructures]]"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "5791040be0ff8b65",
      "text": "- Start with the architecture of **pivotal patterns**/families of patterns - like those highlighted in the college structure map here [[Curriculum of formacion, cutting list of tools]]\n> This is where the DisCO project proposal seems rather back-to-front. Start with language . . the ‘economic language’ of contributions within the DisCO, the pattern language of contributions in commons, the language of dual power, the language of care, the language of the dance of knowing and formacion. In the draft proposal, these come after the more specific proposed project actions, which are inadvisably split into 'cultural' and 'technical' actions.\n\n"
    },
